<br>
Intent-To avoid an Epic to &quot;skip&quot; ahead in the rotation for epic drops.  6 Epic guild members could &quot;help&quot; a smaller guild take down a god when alone they may fail(even 3 or 1 good puller can make a huge difference in Fear/Hate).  This is done simply to take the &quot;guess work&quot; out of IF they could take down the god by themselves.  If they can't take down the god alone they should be calling in the epic up in rotation not using a loop hole where they could invite 6 from the epic of their choice.  (we are taking the &quot;choice&quot; out of the inviting guild's hands simply put.)<br>
<br>
To clarify.  If you want to assist a guild out of friendship that is great as long as the epic guild is called in.  We as epics are put in a hard situation here but we are gaining more access to epic pieces we do need to make some sacrifice somewhere.  We need to IMO have a sink or swim philosophy on this.  Either they do it on their own when a god is up or we help and the Epic on call is called in.<br>
<br>
